Description: A toolkit for designing studies with a restricted mean survival 
    time (RMST) endpoint. This package provides functions to perform 
    power and sample size calculations for two-arm studies, implementing
    several modern, direct RMST modeling approaches from the biostatistical
    literature. Users can select a method based on their study's design and
    assumptions, including flexible additive models with splines
    (Zhang & Schaubel, 2024), simple linear models with IPCW for
    independent censoring (Tian et al., 2014), efficient multiplicative models
    for high-dimensional stratification (Wang et al., 2019), and analytic
    methods for covariate-dependent censoring under a single censoring
    mechanism (Wang & Schaubel, 2018).
